"'''Flatline'''" is a song by American rapper [[B.o.B]], initially released on [[SoundCloud]] in January 2016. "Flatline" is a [[diss song]] aimed at physicist [[Neil DeGrasse Tyson]], whom he had gotten into an argument with on [[Twitter]], over B.o.B's stated belief that [[Flat Earth|the earth is flat]]. In addition to dissing Tyson and expressing belief in a flat earth, the song's lyrics also include other [[conspiracy theories]], including [[Holocaust denial]], "[[Reptilian humanoid|mirror lizards]]", and the belief that [[Freemasons]] are indoctrinating young people. The lyrics to the song refer to science as a cult.<ref name="flatline1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/01/26/bob-rap-flatline-earth|title=B.o.B drops 'Flatline', a rap about how the Earth is definitely flat}}</ref><ref name="flatline2">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/alexknapp/2016/01/26/the-lyrics-to-b-o-b-s-flat-earth-anthem-flatline-with-science-annotations/#43093821b058|title=The Lyrics To B.o.B's Flat Earth Anthem 'Flatline' - With Science Annotations}}</ref><ref name="flatline3">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/b-o-b-responds-to-neil-degrasse-tyson-with-flat-earth-diss-track-20160126|title=B.o.B. Responds to Neil deGrasse Tyson With Flat Earth Diss Track}}</ref><ref name="flatearth4">{{cite web|url=http://radio.com/2016/01/26/b-o-b-takes-flat-earth-theory-to-the-next-level-with-new-track/|title=B.o.B Takes Flat Earth Theory to the Next Level with New Track}}</ref> [[Jonathan Greenblatt]], the CEO of the [[Anti-Defamation League]], issued a statement saying that B.o.B's "lyrics are irresponsible and could potentially promote anti-Semitic beliefs, especially in those people who might already be infected by such notions."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adl.org/news/press-releases/adl-troubled-by-bob-rap-lyrics-promoting-anti-semitic-conspiracy-and-invoking|title=ADL Troubled by B.o.B Rap Lyrics Promoting Anti-Semitic Conspiracy and Invoking Holocaust Denier by Name}}</ref> "Following criticism, B.o.B removed the song from his SoundCloud account, but it survives on YouTube and other sites where it was reposted.<ref name="salon">{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2016/01/27/flat_earth_rapper_b_o_b_has_even_more_extreme_dangerous_views_he_promotes_holocaust_denial/|title="Flat Earth" rapper B.o.B has even more extreme, dangerous views: He promotes Holocaust denial}}</ref> In April 2016, B.o.B included the song on a [[mixtape]] titled ''E.A.R.T.H. (Educational Avatar Reality Training Habitat)'', but the song lyrics had been rewritten as titled as pt. 2.<ref>http://hiphopdx.com/news/id.38470/title.b-o-b-e-a-r-t-h-mixtape-stream-cover-art-tracklist-download</ref><ref>http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bob-earth-new-mixtape.116377.html</ref>
