{{Expand German|topic=geo|date=February 2009|Steinheim an der Murr}}
{{Infobox German location |type = Stadt |image_coa = Wappen Steinheim an der Murr.svg |coordinates = {{coord|48|58|0|N|9|17|0|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} |state = Baden-Württemberg |region = Stuttgart |district = Ludwigsburg |elevation = 200 |area = 23.19 |population = 11841 |Stand = 2006-12-31 |postal_code = 71711 |area_code = 07144 |licence = LB |Gemeindeschlüssel = 08 1 18 070 |NUTS = DE115 |Straße = Marktstraße&nbsp;29 |website = [http://www.stadt-steinheim.de/ www.stadt-steinheim.de] |mayor = Thomas Rosner }}
'''Steinheim an der Murr''' is a town in the [[Ludwigsburg (district)|district of Ludwigsburg]], [[Baden-Württemberg]], [[Germany]]. It is situated on the river [[Murr (river)|Murr]], 9&nbsp;km northeast of [[Ludwigsburg]]. The [[Steinheim Skull]] was found near Steinheim an der Murr.
It is known worldwide for a famous skull of an early human, found there in 1933. This human lived around 250.000 years ago. The original skull is kept in the museum of nature in Stuttgart, while in Steinheim, visitors can see two reproductions of the skull in a small museum.
